            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>[In nomine] Patris et Filii et Spiritu Sancti. Anno Deo propitjo
                        pontificatus domni <persName key="#Popes" ref="#people/1591"
                            >Benedicti</persName>
                        <rs key="#Popes">pape</rs> sede quinto, <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/261">Conradus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperatore</rs> anno [un]detjmo, die sestodetjmo
                        m(ensis) madii, indicione quinta, <placeName ref="#places/594"
                            >Rav(enne</placeName>), in cupa posita iusta tribuna <rs key="#Churches"
                            >basilice</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/1480">Sancti Stefani qui
                            vocatur [Ma]ioris</orgName>. Dum inventus fuisset bonissimis adque
                        inlustrissimis viris necnon bone hopinionis laudab[i]lis famam, corum nomina
                        ec sunt: idest <persName key="#Priests #Abbots #Monks" ref="#people/1574"
                            >Uuidone</persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs> et <rs key="#Monks">monachus</rs> adque
                            <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">mon(asterii)</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Penalty #Wine #Ports #Fluvial_transport #Tolls #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1460">Sancte Marie qui vocatur in <placeName
                                ref="#places/4179">Ponposia</placeName></orgName>, Uuidone presbiter
                        et monachus predicto mon(asterio), Tetbaldus nobili viro viced(omi)no,
                        Geremia filius quondam Liutef[re]dus, Farualdi et Pauli filius quondam Pauli
                        iudex Farualdi, Andreas de Susum, Petrus et Paulo germani filii sui,
                        Stefanus filius Teutji tabell(ionis), Petrus de Rautj, Ioh(anne)s et Alberto
                        et Petrus germani filii sui, Deusdedit filius Tribunus, Ioh(anne)s filius
                        quondam Riculfus tabell(ionis), Petrus filius quondam Petri tabell(ionis) de
                        Pusterula, Aldo tabellio, Paulus filius quondam Petrus Pipere et me presente
                        Romanus qui vocatur Stefanus tabell(io) et haliis; in nostrorum
                        suprascriptorum omnium press(entja) hapreenderunt <persName><name
                                ref="Petrus">Petrus</name></persName> et <persName><name
                                ref="Rainbertus">Raimbertus</name></persName> germani nobili viri,
                        filii quondam bone memorie <persName><name ref="Paulus/de Echila">Paulus qui
                                vocabatur de Echila</name></persName>, virgam in manibus illorum et
                        miserunt eam in manum domno Uuidone umilis presbiter et monachus adque abbas
                        regule mon(asterii) Sancte [Marie qui vocatur in] Pomposia, et in manum
                        suprascripto Stefanus filius quondam Teutji tabell(ionis) avocatori suo, et
                        d[ixerunt: â€˜Ecce ...]cedimus vobis omnes accione et querimonias
                        quantascumque nos abuimus usque mo[do ...] requirendum contra vos
                        suprascripto abbas; et insuper spondimus et obligamus nos nostrosque filios
                        e|redes vobis suprascripto domno abbas tuisque subcessoribus im perpetuum,
                        idest omnes res et pertinentjas illas integras quantascumque pertinuit
                        quondam <persName><name ref="Petrus/de Echila">Petrus qui vocabatur de
                                Ech[i]la</name></persName> tjoni nostro in <rs key="#Fundi"
                            >fundum</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Fundi #Size #Fluvial_transport" ref="#estates/2400"><placeName
                            key="#Fundi #Size #Fluvial_transport">Tjsterna</placeName></geogName>, quod sunt <rs
                            key="#Size">untjas se[x]</rs>, et sex untje in fundum <geogName
                                key="#Fundi #Size #Fluvial_transport" ref="#estates/2401"><placeName key="#Fundi #Size #Fluvial_transport"
                                >Lacuna Cava</placeName></geogName> et omnes perti[ne]ntjas illas
                        que sibi pertinuit in fundum suprascripta nomina et in fundum <geogName
                            key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Wine #Fluvial_transport" ref="#estates/2431"><placeName
                                key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Wine #Fluvial_transport" ref="#places/4878"
                            >Lisiano</placeName></geogName> et in fundum qui vocatur <geogName
                                key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Wine #Fluvial_transport" ref="#estates/2433"><placeName
                                    key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Wine #Fluvial_transport"
                            >Roveritulo</placeName></geogName> et i[n fundum <geogName
                                key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Wine #Fluvial_transport" ref="#estates/2432"><placeName
                                    key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Wine #Fluvial_transport"
                            >P]eritulo</placeName></geogName> et in fundum <geogName
                                key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Wine #Fluvial_transport" ref="#estates/2402"><placeName
                                    key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Wine #Fluvial_transport"
                        >Casoti</placeName></geogName>, cum <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >terris</rs>, <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>, campos et cum omnibus ad
                        predictis rebus pertinentibus, sitas <rs key="#Fines">ter[ritorio</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Wine #Fluvial_transport" ref="#estates/2422"
                            ><placeName key="#Fundi #Landed_possessions #Wine #Fluvial_transport"
                                ref="#places/3515">Livi]ensis</placeName></geogName>, <rs
                            key="#Plebs">plebe</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Plebs" ref="#juridical_persons/3628">Sancti
                            Mercuriali</orgName> et <orgName key="#Plebs"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1494">Sancte Marie in Aqueducto</orgName>. Et
                        licead vobis vestra <rs key="#Fluvial_transport">nave domnicate</rs> de
                        vestri omni egendi et redeundi a <rs key="#Ports">portum</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Ports #Fluvial_transport #Tolls" ref="#estates/2493"
                            >Fenarie</geogName> sine omni intentjonem et <rs key="#Tolls"
                            >ripatico</rs>. Et si nostri omines contra ec facere presumserit et
                        [...] atjonem, post eam nobis congnitum est, facere debemus infra tregintam
                        dierum, et si nos aut nostris filiis vel eredibus aut nostra sumissa vel
                        sumitenda personam vobis vestrisque subcessoribus inquietare vel molestare
                        presum[se]rit, daturi et composituri nos esse promitimus nos nostrosque
                        filios eredes tibi tuisque subcessoribus <rs key="#Penalty">auri libras
                            tres</rs>â€™. Et predicto domno abbas et prefato Stefanus avocatori suo
                        sic atjpiens dicxerunt: â€˜Rogamus vos omnes pro futurum testimoniumâ€™. Hoc
                        factum est sub die et m(ense), indicione suprascripta quinta,
                        Rav(enne).</ab>
                </div>
